	abstract = {A novel approach is presented that couples the "hard computing" features of robust H/sub /spl infin// control with the "soft computing" characteristics of intelligent system identification, and realizes the benefits of both. Radial basis function networks (RBFNs) are used to experimentally identify linear parameter varying (LPV) dynamic models and uncertainty models associated with an active magnetic bearing (AMB) test rig. These models are used to synthesize robust H/sub /spl infin// controllers that are gain-scheduled with rotor setpoint. Experimental results confirm the stability robustness and exceptional tracking performance of these "intelligent robust " controllers.},
