	abstract = {A control system to perform spacecraft attitude maneuvers in the presence of mass parameter uncertainties and disturbances is proposed. The control law consisting of a neural network and linear control logic is designed for the spacecraft to follow a pre-specified reference trajectory. Lyapunov stability theory is used to obtain closed-loop stability conditions. These stability conditions serve as constraints imposed on the on-line tuning of the network adjustable weights in the neural network. Simulation results demonstrate the good tracking characteristics of the proposed control law during spacecraft inertia changes and in presence of disturbances. In addition to the good robustness characteristics, simulation results demonstrate the learning capability of the proposed neural network controller by showing rapid convergence of the network weights.},
